,Recommended,319550,12383251,"Posted: 5 October, 2014",all,victimsofretail,"This is an enjoyable game, that is simple in nature yet hard to master.  Appropriately called 'an arcade game', you aim at the holes on spinning disks with your mouse-pointer while you go progessively faster and faster. For every 100 mph faster, the discs and background change color. Sometimes the disks spin around more than other times, adding extra challenge. There is electronic music that adds to the feel overall. Sometimes you'll find yourself laughing at how good you're doing, or the way the different colors add to the thrillride here, and it is fun, and even spellbinding. It's especially good for a few minutes at a time, and I also find it fun in-between games on days we play a few games on Steam, and I also found it gets you prepared for better focus in other games on those days...which is a bonus, really. If you're looking at this game and thinking about getting it, then by all means, go for it. The appeal stays over time, too."
